  "response": "Yes, an agnostic theist is someone who believes in the existence of a god or gods (theism) but acknowledges that they do not have certainty or definitive knowledge about this belief (agnosticism). \n\nIn other words, an agnostic theist might say:\n\n- \"I believe in God, but I recognize that this belief is a matter of faith rather than something that can be proven or known with certainty.\"\n\nThis stance combines theism (belief in a deity) with agnosticism (the idea that the existence of that deity is unknown or unknowable). It\u2019s a nuanced position that accommodates both faith and skepticism about the limits of human knowledge.",
